# Snickerdoodle product rules

Snickerdoodle is Product 2 in the Racoben Engineering portfolio. ShipCheck is Product 1.

## Brand and routes

- Product name: **`PRODUCT_NAME` in `lib/site.ts`** (currently Snickerdoodle) — import everywhere; do not hardcode
- Route: `/snickerdoodle`
- Intake email: `snickerdoodle@racoben.com`
- Tagline: "One survey. A complete campaign package."

## What we sell

Campaign execution packages — not marketing, copy, AI, or templates.

Every package moves one audience toward one clearly defined action.

## Customer-facing scope (V1)

- Campaign survey → polished human-reviewed campaign execution package
- Mailto intake — no DB, auth, payment, or customer dashboard
- Preserve the v0 UI: warm cream/terracotta palette, Fraunces/Geist, section layout, hero imagery, shadcn/Tailwind styling
- Do not re-scaffold or simplify the UI

## Internal production model

```text
Survey → campaign family → desired action → fact ledger → campaign strategy
→ asset map → draft → critique → polish → QA → Rachel review → package
```

- Josh + ChatGPT + custom AI tooling draft/adapt/critique/polish/package
- Rachel is the **final expert quality gate**, not the first drafter

## Hard rules

- **AI is internal only.** Never customer-facing AI, chat, prompts, or model settings.
- **Fact ledger only.** AI must not invent sponsors, donation matches, statistics, quotes, links, partners, deadlines, outcomes, or claims.
- **Human review required** before every delivery.

## Do not add (V1)

- customer-facing AI
- chat or prompt interfaces
- auth / database / payment integration
- customer dashboard or automated delivery portal
- email sending platform or social posting automation
- analytics that stores personal/project data
- RacobenStudio implementation in this repo

## Key files

- `lib/site.ts` — brand constants, basePath prefix, intake email
- `lib/intake.ts` — survey form schema and mailto formatting
- `docs/operating-doctrine.md` — product philosophy
- `docs/campaign-families.md` — launch campaign families
- `docs/internal-automation-pipeline.md` — staff production workflow
- `docs/fact-ledger.md` — single source of truth for AI drafting
- `docs/editor-packet.md` — Rachel review bundle spec
- `fulfillment/` — pipeline, QA, delivery, internal prompts

## Deploy

- Standalone Vercel project with `basePath: '/snickerdoodle'`
- Parent Racoben site rewrites `/snickerdoodle` and `/snickerdoodle/*` via `SNICKERDOODLE_PRODUCTION_URL` (no path suffix in env var)
